The Senate and House of Representatives yesterday approved the report of the conference committee on the 2018 budget. At the Senate, the chairman of the Senate committee on Appropriation, Senator Danjuma Goje (APC, Gombe) presented the report. He said out of the six differing clauses, the panel adopted four of the Senate and two of the House. In the House of Representatives, the report of the harmonization committee was laid on the floor at the beginning of plenary by the chairman of the appropriation committee, Mustapha Bala Dawaki (APC, Kano). After considering other items on the Order Paper, the report was adopted at the end of the plenary with Speaker Yakubu Dogara presiding. Dawaki had told the House that the Conference Committee reached agreements on the deferring clauses.